<b>Charm Kiting - </b>5/8/01 12:55:01 AM<br>~ <b>Fyrsong Bloodyears</b><blockquote>Are you one of those who's heard that bards can't solo?<br><br>Here's a new best friend for you.<br><br>With this song, you can easily solo 2 hill giants at a time.  They call level 40 a hell level.  Drop 2 hill giants at a time, and you'll go through lvl 40 in no time flat and still, not have to worry about mana like those caster types who solo.<br><br>Simply pull your first mob, do a bit of damage to it with your 38 song, then find another one, and charm it.  Once the charmed mob agro's on your first, slightly damaged mob, it will do the work for you.  No need to run in circles because they will both battle it out.  If you're paying attention, your charmed mob will win, and you will have a near dead pet to finish off yourself with your Chant song.  <br><br>Works great with hill giants.  I can usually do about 8 in a row before I need to heal up.  Very fun stuff.  <br><br>Beware though.  You'll have many people trying to 'save' you because they think you're in trouble with 2 mobs chasing you.  <br>Good luck!</blockquote></td></tr></table></blockquote><br><br><br><br><br><br><a href="/songs.asp?&song=45">Back to Normal Mode</a><br><br><br><i>Printed from EQDiva.com on 1/16/03 4:50:32 PM.</i><br><br></td></tr></table>
